<item>
 <title>The Tangled Web We Weave</title>
 <link>http://www.theworldisnotflat.com/tangled-web</link>
 <description>  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;We are both continually amazed at how having this web site has connected us with people we would have otherwise never known.&amp;nbsp; Just a couple of nights ago, we had dinner with the sister of a friend&amp;rsquo;s former roommate, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kirkandmaria.com/&quot;&gt;Maria&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp; I was asked her in an email how in the world she knew about us. Here is the connection&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Maria was a housemate with my long time friend JJ in &lt;st1:city&gt;&lt;st1:place&gt;Seattle&lt;/st1:place&gt;&lt;/st1:city&gt; (1999-2002).&amp;nbsp; We met a few times, but only at parties etc. A couple of years ago, JJ moved to &lt;st1:place&gt;S. Carolina&lt;/st1:place&gt; and Maria lost touch, so she recently Googled him, hoping to make contact. &amp;nbsp;She then found &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.leelefever.com/archives/000210.html&quot;&gt;a blog post&lt;/a&gt; from me about his wedding in 2003.&amp;nbsp; While reading about his wedding, she noticed a reminder that Sachi and I were traveling around the world and started reading TwinF. &amp;nbsp;Once she saw us reach &lt;st1:city&gt;&lt;st1:place&gt;Barcelona&lt;/st1:place&gt;&lt;/st1:city&gt;, she contacted her sister Camila, who got a group of her friends from business school to take us to their favorite local tapas bar in &lt;st1:city&gt;&lt;st1:place&gt;Barcelona&lt;/st1:place&gt;&lt;/st1:city&gt;&amp;rsquo;s Gracia neighborhood. &amp;nbsp;Though we only barely know Maria, the tiny connection was enough to help us make new friends in a foreign country. Thanks Maria and Camila! &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://static.flickr.com/112/302344365_926b475f9b.jpg?v=0&quot; onload=&quot;show_notes_initially();&quot; class=&quot;reflect&quot; height=&quot;375&quot; width=&quot;500&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;If this wasn&amp;rsquo;t enough, Maria also reminded us that we help her brother too&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;blockquote&quot;&gt;My brother Fernando and his wife printed out all your &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.theworldisnotflat.com/tags/thailand&quot;&gt;&lt;st1:country-region&gt;&lt;st1:place&gt;Thailand&lt;/st1:place&gt;&lt;/st1:country-region&gt; dispatches&lt;/a&gt; and read them on the plane to &lt;st1:country-region&gt;&lt;st1:place&gt;Thailand&lt;/st1:place&gt;&lt;/st1:country-region&gt; in early September.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Crazy. We both think it is pretty amazing that suddenly, because of blogs and the Internet that these sorts of connections are possible. What a world in which we live. What a world.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;br class=&quot;clear&quot; /&gt;</description>
